 Bachelor’s degree 
 7 - 10 years of public relations experience 
 Business-to-business technology PR experience required 
 Current experience managing media relationships, and a network of media contacts 
 Experience supporting large press events required 
 3-5 years of experience in business critical communications 
 Portfolio of work demonstrating successful placement of B2B technology stories in mainstream, business, and tech trade publications. 
 
Amazon Web Services (AWS) seeks an experienced Machine Learning (ML) and Artificial Intelligence (AI) public relations professional who is creative, self-motivated, high-judgment, and well-connected to drive communications programs for a high-profile portfolio of services. The right candidate possesses deep familiarity with AI/ML technology, extensive media relations experience, is comfortable leading a dynamic and global PR program, is an expert at translating complex technology concepts and their impact into digestible stories, and can exercise high judgment while acting quickly.
 
The AWS PR Manager partners with AWS AI/ML service, business, and marketing teams, along with a global team of PR, policy, legal, and science colleagues to develop and execute messaging, PR strategy, and innovative communications tactics. The ideal candidate enjoys diving deep into AI/ML technology and is motivated by a dynamic, highly creative culture where the challenge of breaking new ground and redefining best practices is welcome. In this role, the candidate will have an opportunity to innovate new and interesting communications and influencer relations strategies. The candidate must be comfortable working sensitive issues, thoughtfully educating others, and communicating with the media on topics that can impact AWS’s reputation.
 
Since 2006, AWS has changed the way that companies acquire and use technology by providing a highly-scalable, cost-effective, energy-efficient, and flexible technology platform in the cloud. Today, AWS is doing the same for machine learning and artificial intelligence services, enabling every developer and data scientist across all industries and business sizes to leverage the same sophisticated AI/ML technology Amazon.com has been pioneering for more than two decades. Customers in the U.S. and around the world, from startups to Fortune 500 enterprises, are using AWS machine learning and artificial intelligence services to reinvent their businesses, optimize their operations, create new experiences for consumers, and solve some of the world’s toughest challenges.
 
This role can be located in Seattle or HQ2 (Arlington/DC) and requires periodic travel.
 
 Responsibilities: 
There are hundreds of journalists worldwide who are trying to understand and help their readers understand emerging AI/ML technologies. To help achieve this, the AWS PR Manager will:
 
 Define, develop, and oversee end-to-end execution of a business critical communications program 
 Deliver strategic counsel to business leadership, executive, and public policy teams 
 Regularly interact with senior leadership to influence strategy and negotiate decisions in relation to service issues, announcements, and messaging. 
 Serve as a global liaison for international PR teams, helping to support international plans, service launches, and cross-functional PR campaigns 
 Develop and strengthen relationships with key journalists, bloggers, and evaluators in AI, technology trade, and business press 
 Ensure factually accurate representation of AWS services in the press 
 Manage sensitive reputational issues with internal stakeholders and member of the media 
 Manage complex, fast-moving, and unexpected communications challenges with high judgment and professionalism. 
 Protect sensitive competitive, technical, business-confidential information 
 Proven experience with business-critical communications and issues management 
 A track record of successfully representing high-profile enterprise Information Technology products, energy utilities or technology companies 
 Outstanding attention to detail, understanding of technology and the efficiency of cloud computing, and ability to communicate complex topics effectively 
 Excellent writing skills 
 Thrives in a collaborative environment and is willing to roll up their sleeves to get the job done 
 Creativity and bias for action 
 Strong judgment and the ability to respond quickly, yet thoughtfully, to urgent PR matters 
 A knack for diplomacy and the confidence to engage and build consensus with functional leaders at all levels 
 
